	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok so I have read all these posts above and I'm bored so I'll just give ya'll my take on the whole thing.<br>If you're botting a shammy then you prolly aren't doing major raids so you must be referring to xp groups.<br>At least I would not want to bot a shammy cuz I find myself too precoccupied with everything going on when I'm raiding somewhere.<br>As far as xp groups goes you should always buff the melees with all the buffs you can.&nbsp;&nbsp;Yeah they take a lot of mana but so what--shammies run through mana like water, and we're the best at getting it back.<br>Keep regen on yourself and all others like others here have stated.<br>Hos or focus the melee, and put whatever hp buff you can on the cleric and chanter.<br>Most people go to one of the pop now since it's the best xp, and this is what I've learned so far.<br>ALWAYS use maloxxx first before you slow.<br>I don't care if it resists 5 times in a row make it stick.<br>Aggro from a resisted slow sucks, and if the mob isn't slowed chances are you will die.  Aggro from maloxxx is next to nil, and a mob can be taunted off of you easy.  And when it's slowed, who cares if it's aggro'd you.<br>Granted I don't have the best hps in the world, but fully buffed at 3.5khps those neat little creepers and crocs in pon will eat me in no time if I fail to slow it, and after you prolly your cleric.<br>Actually was grouped with another 59 shammy today who got all upset when slow aggro got him whacked.  I told him to use malosini and he told me if the warrior was taunting he wouldnt have gotten aggro.  That has to be the stupidest thing I have ever heard anyone say.  As a shaman YOU should be the one deciding how much aggro you have.  About the only thing that can pull a po'd mob off me is a chanter casting tash, which is one of the reasons I specifically request them not to cast it unless they absolutely have to.<br>Always keep the &quot;not-quite-ch&quot; spell memmed.<br>Who knows when you gonna have a bad pull and the cleric has to chain cast ethereal light or some such to keep everyone alive.<br>As for DS potions...what's the point?<br>I mean, honestly...<br>Sure you get a lil xtra damage every few seconds but if you need that damage to kill the mobs you shouldn't be in pop.<br>Remember DS works best when the mobs are goin full speed and if you must have a ds then let the druid or mage or whatever handle that.<br>As far as canni-dancin well, you might want to stand a little longer in pop than you are used to in other zones because that 600-1k damage they did to you for that instant you sat lost you 320-500 or so mana that could have been harvested with can4.<br>Wait till the mob is below 2 bubs or so of life before you even think about sitting, and then just pop down and up to see if the mob will turn toward you.<br>Oh, and play in 3rd person as much as you can.<br>I know it's hard to get used to but you will eventually come to find first person too constrictive.<br>3rd person perspective let's you keep an eye on the whole picture and see those sneaky bastard mobs that like to hide under docks or come flyin off from god knows where.<br>I know I'm jumpin around here but bear with me.<br>Oh, and as for dotting/nuking well, we have some really crappy dps so if you want to help out keep nife memmed and summon your dog.<br>Doggy should be all you really use anyhow unless your group has crappy dps...our dots dont really scratch up the mobs all too bad in pop.<br>Save your extra mana for heals, and yes DO heal yourself if you got aggro and about to die.<br>Use that nice chloroblast spell, it has saved me on more than one occasion.<br>Your spells will not get interrupted all that much contrary to what one of the above posters said and chloro is fast.<br>Even faster if you smart enuf to have the cleric cast blessing of faith on you before you start fighting.<br>Sometimes that little heal is all the difference between that Ethereal Light hitting you and it hitting your corpse.<br>But don't run around, makes it hard for the tanks to taunt it off.<br>And so EVERYONE knows, PETS DONT BREAK MEZ!!!<br>I'll say it again...<br>PETS DON'T BREAK MEZ!!!<br>It was posted in one of the patch messages, and confirmed to me by a gm on my server, Povar.<br>If something is breaking mez it's either one of the idiot melee, a druid using their damage-inflicting root, or a necro's dot.<br>That little message we get that says, &quot;sorry master, I am unable to awaken TARGET&quot; means exactly that.<br>I'm so tired of some chanter doing a crappy job, or dumb melee breaking mez and tryin to pass it off as my pet's fault.<br>Stick to your guns and pay attention to the other people in your group.<br>Chances are one of them can't get out of their HHP mentality and own up to their stupid mistakes.<br>Ok I'm starting to ramble so /q.<br><br>Mephista<br>59 Shaman<br>Povar<br>&nbsp;<br>Mephista D`Monica<br>&lt;Seraphims Vengeance&gt;<br>Povar<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=617033" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=617033</a></td></tr>
