	   <tr><td colspan=2>&nbsp;&nbsp; Here's some good tricks to know for anyone reading this thread who may not know some stuff about shamans or the game yet. First I will say that in some cases for a shaman getting aggro is the best defense/offense thing to do.<br><br>  Offensively for instance if the only melee in the group or still alive is a rogue you want the aggro so they can backstab. You can also offtank slowed mobs or pull off other casters if needed with a dot or a nuke or a slow if the mob isn't slowed yet. Obviously I don't suggest this unless you have a fairly decent ac/ hps vs the mobs attack. I usually only offtank casters who have broken mezz and been mana drained/used up their mana.<br> <br> When you slow it's not good to sit down sometimes in groups. So often if mana is good, it's ok to throw your spear or your hammer into the fray and take the risk of getting hit once or twice since you should have regen up anyway. If you are using bear form and tanking shrink yourself. You can also cast canni if your not getting aggro while you are tanking. This may sound suicidal but if you use a weapon like the howling harpoon the stun proc is worth the effort and you don't get much aggro. If you have or are using a decent damage output weapon like the epic, winterstorm or the rune etched ice wurm fang I suggest waiting a tick or two for the real tanks to get some decent aggro.<br><br>   Make a hotkey for mobs you dot they can't be mezzed if they are dotted this is to let the chanter know what to mezz and the tanks to know what to focus on. This also lets people know how you are using your mana and gives them a general idea of how tough the mob is.<br><br>    Pet kiting or pet + tank kiting is a good method to prevent people from getting hurt. I did a fair amount of hunting in burning woods with a warrior friend and this is how it usually went. If there were two mobs hitting him I would slow both dot one to get it's aggro and root it. If it broke root i would run it around until he was done, reroot it or tank it. If it was a named baddie like gorgul patlock that was an add or a problem due to mana I would get the aggro he would taunt it I would sit to get aggro back and gain mana and move before it hit me. He and the pet would attack it from behind, thus increasing our damage per second and decreasing its. This also works with a pet although not as well. <br><br>  As far as using root goes it's a judgement call on the situation if a mob is rooted it will keep hitting people or pets that are tanking it when otherwise it would turn and run. On the flipside, It also won't run off and bring friends to the party.<br><br>   Also good to know is that your char affects your resist chance of slows and dots etc. Always keep your charisma buffed on mobs you are getting resisted on. Our debuffs work as well as an enchanters but often their char is higher(affecting their ability to debuff) in the everyday situation because they are more charisma dependent than we are. With up to 6 mobs mezzed checking against your charisma every tick you'd want a high charisma too. So the best combo is to have them tash for the slows when neccessary(slow goes against mr even though it can be cured like a disease). I had a great crypt group last night where we did this against the emperor(lvl 60 mob) and it worked really well both of us lvl 54. If you know ahead of time that your gonna need it buy some straight charisma stuff. It's worth losing 100 or more out of your mana pool to be able to overcome one or more resists of a 250 mana turgurs.<br><br>  One other thing before I go hps are as valuable as wisdom/mana to shamans if not more so because they will keep you alive and allow you to be safer when you use your canni. It's worth losing 25 mana out of your pool for 50+ hps. This is the ratio of canni conversion which gets slightly better at each step up. It's great having a big pool for buffing a raid party, but in exp groups getting mana back is the key thing.<br><br>Ok enough now gotta run :-)<br><br>Arnoldofgaul<br>54 shaman erollisi marr<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
